Package: aruleRec
Title: Easy and fast Recommendations With Association Rule Learning in R
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Henrik", "Varmer", email = "henrik@varmer.dk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The aruleRec function takes a dataframe as input in tidy (long) format with one observation (customer-item pair) per row. This data.frame must contain two columns: a customer ID and a product ID. The data.frame and column names must be provided as arguments to the function, along with the hyperparameters for association rule mining: confidence, support, minlen, and maxlen..
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5.1),
    dplyr (>= 0.7.1),
    arules,
    tidyr
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    dplyr,
    arules,
    tidyr
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
